# typography.rules.md

### A. Purpose
Establish a consistent, scalable type system for all Khwarizmi products. Ensures readability, hierarchy, and Arabic-first typographic behavior across enterprise interfaces.

### B. Rules
- Typography must follow a **modular scale** â€” no arbitrary font sizes.
- Defined scale (in px / rem):
  - **Display**: 57px / 3.5625rem â€” hero headings only
  - **H1**: 32px / 2rem
  - **H2**: 24px / 1.5rem
  - **H3**: 20px / 1.25rem
  - **H4**: 16px / 1rem (semibold)
  - **Body Large**: 16px / 1rem (regular)
  - **Body Medium**: 14px / 0.875rem (regular)
  - **Body Small / Caption**: 12px / 0.75rem
  - **Label**: 11px / 0.6875rem (uppercase, tracked)
- Line height: 1.5Ă— font size minimum for body text; 1.2Ă— for headings.
- Arabic typeface must be explicitly specified and must be an enterprise-grade Arabic font (e.g. Cairo, IBM Plex Arabic, Noto Kufi Arabic).
- Latin typeface pairing must complement the Arabic face (e.g. Inter, IBM Plex Sans).
- Font weight scale: 400 (regular), 500 (medium), 600 (semibold), 700 (bold) only.
- No decorative or display fonts in data-heavy interfaces.
- Text on colored backgrounds must use the corresponding `--color-sf-on-{role}` token.
- Do not justify Arabic text in UI components â€” use `start` alignment (right for RTL).
- Truncation with ellipsis must be applied to all single-line overflow situations.
- Minimum body text size: 14px for desktop, 16px for mobile.
- Line length for readable prose: 60â€“80 characters (max 90).

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- âś… Use H1â€“H4 in strict hierarchy â€” never skip levels.
- âś… Apply Arabic font to all Arabic content, including labels and placeholders.
- âś… Use Body Medium (14px) as the default for tables, forms, and list items.
- âś… Use Caption (12px) for metadata, timestamps, helper text.
- âś… Use Label (11px uppercase) for column headers and section dividers.
- âś… Apply `font-feature-settings: "kern", "liga"` for Arabic shaping support.

**Don't:**
- âťŚ Do not use font sizes outside the defined scale.
- âťŚ Do not center-align Arabic paragraph text.
- âťŚ Do not use italic for Arabic â€” it is not a valid Arabic typographic style.
- âťŚ Do not apply letter-spacing to Arabic text.
- âťŚ Do not use more than two typefaces in a single interface.
- âťŚ Do not use font weight 300 (light) in enterprise interfaces â€” it reduces readability.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating text elements, always assign the correct type scale role (H1, Body Medium, Caption, etc.).
- Detect language context: apply Arabic typeface for RTL content, Latin typeface for LTR.
- When generating table headers, default to Label style (11px uppercase, semibold).
- When generating form labels, use Body Small (12px, medium weight).
- Do not infer font size from visual appearance â€” always reference the scale.

