- âťŚ Do not use any other UI library (MUI, Ant, Chakra, shadcn, Radix).
- âťŚ Do not override Syncfusion internal class names directly.
- âťŚ Do not import Fluent, Bootstrap, or Tailwind theme â€” Material-3 only.
- âťŚ Do not disable Syncfusion's built-in accessibility attributes.
- âťŚ Do not use Syncfusion component markup outside its documented API.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating any UI element, first identify its Syncfusion Material-3 component equivalent.
- Reference the Syncfusion UI Kit Figma file for design specs: `https://www.figma.com/community/file/1454123774600129202`
- When generating code, always use the Syncfusion component import path: `@syncfusion/ej2-react-*` (React) or `@syncfusion/ej2-*` (JS).
- Enable RTL globally at app root: `L10n.load()` + `setCulture('ar')` + `enableRtl(true)` for Arabic interfaces.
