# tables.rules.md

### A. Purpose
Define all rules for data table design and behavior using Syncfusion Material-3 grid components exclusively.

### B. Rules

**Component Selection:**
- All tabular data â†’ `SfGrid` (Syncfusion Data Grid)
- Hierarchical data â†’ `SfTreeGrid`
- Cross-tabular analytics â†’ `SfPivotView`
- Editable spreadsheet-style â†’ `SfSpreadsheet`
- Pagination control â†’ `SfPager`

**Structure:**
- Column headers: Label style (11px, uppercase, semibold, `--color-sf-on-surface-variant`)
- Row height: 40px compact / 48px default / 56px relaxed
- Cell padding: 12px vertical, 16px horizontal
- Alternating rows: `--color-sf-on-surface-opacity4` for alternate row (use `SfGrid` `enableAltRow` prop)
- Selected row: `--color-sf-primary-opacity-8` (Syncfusion applies via Material-3 theme)
- Hover row: `--color-sf-on-surface-opacity5` (handled by Material-3 theme)

**Required SfGrid Features (always enable):**
- Sorting: `allowSorting={true}`
- Filtering: `allowFiltering={true}` with FilterBar or Menu filter
- Pagination: `allowPaging={true}` with `SfPager`
- Column resizing: `allowResizing={true}`
- Column reorder: `allowReordering={true}`
- RTL: handled globally via `enableRtl(true)`

**Conditional Features (enable when applicable):**
- Selection with bulk actions: `selectionSettings={{ type: 'Multiple', checkboxMode: 'ResetOnRowClick' }}`
- Export (CSV / Excel / PDF): `SfGrid` toolbar with `['ExcelExport', 'CsvExport', 'PdfExport']`
- Column chooser: `showColumnChooser={true}` when table > 8 columns
- Frozen columns: `freeze` prop on identifier/name column when > 8 columns
- Virtual scrolling: `enableVirtualization={true}` for datasets > 500 rows
- Inline editing: `editSettings={{ allowEditing: true, mode: 'Normal' }}` using `SfInPlaceEditor`
- Search: `toolbar={['Search']}` above the grid

**Content Rules:**
- Empty cells: display `â€”` (en dash) â€” set via `defaultValue` or template
- Numbers: right-aligned in LTR, left-aligned (reading-end) in RTL
- Text: right-aligned in RTL (automatic with `enableRtl`)
- Dates: `DD/MM/YYYY` format for Arabic contexts â€” set via `SfGrid` column `format` prop
- Status columns: use `SfBadge` or `SfChip` via column template â€” never raw text
- Action columns: always last column (leftmost in RTL) â€” use `SfButton` icon-only or `SfContextMenu`
- Max visible columns without column chooser: 10

**Accessibility:**
- `SfGrid` includes `role="grid"` and full ARIA support by default â€” do not remove.
- Keyboard: Tab between cells, Arrow keys within grid, Enter to activate â€” built into `SfGrid`.
- Sort announcement via `aria-sort` is handled automatically by Syncfusion.

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- âś… Use `SfGrid` for all structured data â€” never custom `<table>` HTML.
- âś… Freeze the identifier column when > 8 columns.
- âś… Show row count and `SfPager` at bottom.
- âś… Use `SfBadge` or `SfChip` in status columns.
- âś… Enable column chooser for complex tables.
- âś… Use `SfGrid` export toolbar for report contexts.

**Don't:**
- âťŚ Do not build custom table markup.
- âťŚ Do not display more than 10 unsorted columns without column chooser.
- âťŚ Do not use plain text in status columns.
- âťŚ Do not load all records without pagination or virtual scrolling.
- âťŚ Do not place full action button sets in every row â€” use `SfContextMenu` instead.
- âťŚ Do not override Syncfusion grid CSS classes directly.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating a data table, default to `SfGrid` with sorting, filtering, and pagination enabled.
- Auto-apply: Label headers, 48px row height, 12px/16px cell padding, RTL alignment via `enableRtl`.
- When generating status columns, auto-generate `SfBadge` or `SfChip` template variants per status value.
- For datasets > 500 rows, enable `enableVirtualization`.
- For report contexts, add export toolbar: `['Search', 'ExcelExport', 'PdfExport', 'CsvExport']`.
- Map Figma frame column specs to `SfGrid` column definitions: field, headerText, width, textAlign, template.
- Always generate an empty state template for the grid using `SfSkeleton` during load.



