# feedback.rules.md

### A. Purpose
Standardize all system feedback patterns using Syncfusion UI Kit â€” Material-3 Theme components exclusively.

### B. Rules

**Component â†’ Use Case Mapping:**
- `SfToast` â†’ transient, non-blocking post-action feedback. Auto-dismiss 4â€“6 seconds. Position: bottom-left (RTL default â€” `position: { X: 'Left', Y: 'Bottom' }`)
- `SfMessage` â†’ persistent inline contextual alerts within page content. Do not auto-dismiss.
- `SfBadge` â†’ count and status indicators on navigation items and avatars only.
- `SfProgressBar` â†’ determinate or indeterminate long-running operations.
- `SfSkeleton` â†’ ALL loading states for content areas. Never show empty containers.
- `SfSpinner` â†’ small, localized loading: button loading state, inline action only.
- `SfDialog` (Confirm variant / Predefined) â†’ destructive action confirmation (delete, discard, logout).

**Semantic Role Mapping:**
- Success â†’ `SfToast`/`SfMessage` with `cssClass='e-success'` + `--color-sf-success-container`
- Warning â†’ `cssClass='e-warning'` + `--color-sf-warning-container`
- Error/Danger â†’ `cssClass='e-error'` + `--color-sf-error-container`
- Info â†’ `cssClass='e-info'` + `--color-sf-info-container`

**Validation Feedback:**
- Inline validation below field via `FormValidator` â€” Body Small (12px), error color token
- Validate on blur and on form submit â€” not on every keystroke
- Error messages: describe what is wrong AND how to fix it. Never "Invalid input."
- Required field marker: `*` after label text
- Form-level errors on submit: `SfMessage` (error variant) at top of form

**Empty States:**
- Every empty state: icon + title + description + primary `SfButton` action
- Constructive message â€” explain why empty and what user can do
- Never display raw "No data" text
- Use `SfSkeleton` during loading before the empty state is confirmed

**Error States:**
- Network/API errors: `SfMessage` (error) with retry `SfButton`
- 404: custom page with `SfButton` back to safe location
- Table/grid errors: inline `SfMessage` above `SfGrid` or row-level template
- Never display raw error codes or stack traces

**Loading States:**
- Content areas: `SfSkeleton` â€” always
- Button actions: `SfSpinner` inside `SfButton` + disable button
- Page-level bulk operations: `SfProgressBar` with percentage or step label
- Real-time status: `SfBadge` updates or `SfToast` â€” never rely on page refresh

**SfToast Stacking:**
- Maximum 3 simultaneous toasts â€” queue overflow beyond that
- Use `newestOnTop: true` for stacking order

### C. Do / Don't

**Do:**
- âś… Use `SfToast` for all post-action feedback (save, create, delete confirmed).
- âś… Use `SfSkeleton` during ALL content loading states.
- âś… Provide actionable error messages via `FormValidator` and `SfMessage`.
- âś… Use `SfDialog` Confirm variant before any irreversible action.
- âś… Apply `cssClass` semantic variants (`e-success`, `e-error`, `e-warning`, `e-info`).

**Don't:**
- âťŚ Do not use browser `alert()` or `confirm()` dialogs.
- âťŚ Do not show empty containers without `SfSkeleton` or empty state.
- âťŚ Do not stack more than 3 `SfToast` simultaneously.
- âťŚ Do not use `e-warning` for errors or `e-info` for success.
- âťŚ Do not validate on every keystroke â€” blur/submit only.
- âťŚ Do not display technical error messages or stack traces to users.
- âťŚ Do not use `SfSpinner` for full content area loading â€” use `SfSkeleton`.

### D. MCP Usage Guidance
- When generating forms, always include `FormValidator` with error state variants.
- When generating loading states, auto-insert `SfSkeleton` for all content containers.
- When generating action buttons (delete, submit), auto-pair with `SfDialog` Confirm variant.
- Map feedback intent to Syncfusion component + cssClass: saved â†’ `SfToast e-success`, failed â†’ `SfMessage e-error`, processing â†’ `SfProgressBar`.
- Always generate empty state treatment alongside any `SfGrid`, `SfListView`, or data container.
- Reference Syncfusion Material-3 toast/message specs from Figma Kit for sizing and spacing.



